Task 1: Install and Configure Gophish
Step 1: Download Gophish
# Update system and install dependencies
sudo apt update && sudo apt install wget unzip -y

# Create working directory
mkdir ~/gophish && cd ~/gophish

# Download Gophish (v0.12.1)
wget https://github.com/gophish/gophish/releases/download/v0.12.1/gophish-v0.12.1-linux-64bit.zip

# Extract and set permissions
unzip gophish-v0.12.1-linux-64bit.zip
chmod +x gophish
Step 2: Configure Gophish Settings
Edit the configuration file to set appropriate listening addresses:

# Backup original config
cp config.json config.json.bak

# Edit config.json to change admin interface binding
# Change "listen_url": "127.0.0.1:3333" to "0.0.0.0:3333" if needed
nano config.json
Key configuration parameters:

admin_server.listen_url: Admin interface address (default: 127.0.0.1:3333)
phish_server.listen_url: Phishing server address (default: 0.0.0.0:80)
db_name: Database type (sqlite3)
Step 3: Start Gophish
# Start Gophish
./gophish

# Note the initial admin password displayed in terminal output
# Example: "Please login with the username admin and the password 4304d5255378177d"
Step 4: Access Admin Interface
Open browser and navigate to http://localhost:3333
Login with username admin and the password from terminal
Change the default password immediately
Generate an API key: Account Settings → Reset API Key
