Troubleshooting Tips
Issue: Gophish won't start or shows port binding error

Solution: Check if ports 3333 and 80 are already in use
Run: sudo netstat -tulpn | grep -E '3333|80'
Kill conflicting processes or change ports in config.json
Issue: Emails not being sent

Solution: Verify SMTP configuration and credentials
Test SMTP connectivity: telnet smtp-server 25
Check Gophish logs for detailed error messages
Ensure firewall allows outbound SMTP connections
Issue: Landing page not capturing credentials

Solution: Verify form method is POST and includes {{.Tracker}}
Check "Capture Submitted Data" is enabled in landing page settings
Ensure form field names are present (username, password)
Issue: API authentication fails

Solution: Regenerate API key in Account Settings
Verify API key is correctly copied (no extra spaces)
Check API URL format: http://localhost:3333/api
Issue: Campaign shows "Error Sending Email"

Solution: Verify target email addresses are valid
Check SMTP server allows relay from your IP
Review SMTP authentication credentials
Test with a single target first before bulk sending
